name: Oree
trivia: Oree’s name is derived from orejas (ear in Spanish) and electronic.
Oree is mentioned in The creation of Digital Temtem.
Oree is the starter Temtem for the player’s rival, Max.
Oree was the first Digital Temtem to appear in the game.
gameDescription: One of the first prototypes created in Nanto Labs, Oree's early versions were the forerunners of Digital Temtem. Inquisitive creatures by design, they show great curiosity and a boundless appetite for information.

name: Zaobian
trivia: Zaobian's name is derived from zhào (megabyte in Chinese) and túbiàn (mutation in Chinese).
gameDescription: Zaobian are part of the second generation of Digital Temtem. Created with much more refined technology, they are more intelligent friends and companions, as well as sturdier in battle. citation needed

name: Platypet
trivia: Platypet’s name is derived from platypus and pet.

Platypet is a Breeder Tier Temtem by PokéNinja, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. It was drawn by 50 Shades of Heliolisk. Crema and PokéNinja obtained the rights to add Platypet, Platox and Platimous to the game.
Platypet's Luma color was chosen based on a community vote by PokéNinja.
Platypet was known as Pettans in early development.
Platypet has the lowest Defense stat of all currently available Temtem.
gameDescription: Platypet was popularised by a cartoon series, and ever since then it has been one of the most popular Temtem with kids. The series had an educative purpose: to teach children that Toxic Temtem are also valid and can be good friends.

name: Platox
trivia: Platox is a Breeder Tier Temtem by PokéNinja, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. It was drawn by 50 Shades of Heliolisk. Crema and PokéNinja obtained the rights to add Platypet, Platox and Platimous to the game.
Platox' Luma color was chosen based on a community vote by PokéNinja.
Platox' name is derived from platypus and toxic.
Platox has the highest base stat total of any Temtem that is not in its final evolutionary stage.
gameDescription: Platox share common ancestors with Saipat, but the species diverged centuries ago - while Saipat developed opposable thumbs, Platox specialized in surviving polluted environments. Today they are the most successful feathered Temtem of Tucma.

name: Platimous
trivia: Platimous is a Breeder Tier Temtem by PokéNinja, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. It was drawn by 50 Shades of Heliolisk. Crema and PokéNinja obtained the rights to add Platypet, Platox and Platimous to the game.
Platimous' Luma color was chosen based on a community vote by PokéNinja.
Platimous' name is derived from platypus and either venomous or enormous.
gameDescription: Charles Temwin described them as "Platox, but more so". This is usually taken as classic Arburian understatement - Platimous were amongst the most successful apex predators before large scale taming, and remain very effective fighters.

name: Swali
trivia: Swali's name is derived from swaddle and ali (wing in Italian).
Swali was shown for the first time on iNinjaHero's 08/08/2018 Twitch stream, during his visit to Crema HQ.
Swali's description and in-game footage was first shown on the official Temtem Twitter.
gameDescription: When the harvest season is on, Omninesian fruit-pickers are always careful not to accidentally damage the delicate, chrysalis-like Swali. They grow on certain vines of the rainforest canopy, dropping to the jungle floor once mature and mobile.

name: Loali
trivia: Loali's name is derived from lot of ali (wing in Italian).
Loali was recolored many times before the final look was chosen, as depicted in its concept art.
In Temtem lore, it is the symbol of peace and harmony.
A Loali is given to the player as a part of the main story quest: Shipwrecked in Tucma!
gameDescription: Delicate and graceful creatures, Loali are all wings and eyes - and natural charmers. Their hypnotic eyes can completely dazzle their enemies and their constantly fluttering wings allow them to change course in an instant.

name: Tateru
trivia: Tateru's name comes from tateru (Japanese for stand/erect: 立てる).
Tateru was first revealed through its color test concept art.
Tateru was recolored many times before the final look was chosen, as depicted in its concept art.
Tateru has an emote on the official Temtem Discord. It portrays a police officer.

Tateru took over Temtem and became the CEO for one day on April 1st, 2020. It made several comical tweets and several other Tateru invaded the Discord chats before retiring at the end of the day due to being tired.
gameDescription: Despite their impressive height, Tateru are quite shy and not naturally aggressive. That's why they need proper training before battle. Wild Tateru are recognized for their upright position and sensitive antennae, always alert.

name: Paharo
trivia: Paharo's name is derived  from Pájaro (Spanish for bird) with a South Spanish accent.
Paharo was first revealed via Twitter.
As of Alpha 0.6.4, Paharo has the lowest base Stamina stat of all Temtem at 18.
Paharo is the lightest Temtem currently available.
gameDescription: Paharo tend to hide in treetops and lurk, their green "mask" allowing them to blend in with the foliage. Often the only way to locate them is to look for the telltale gleam of their eyes.

name: Paharac
trivia: Paharac's name comes from pajarraco (Spanish for big bird).
Paharac was first seen on the Temtem banners.
Paharac was first revealed on the 13th June 2018, during a Twitch interview hosted by PokéNinja and the CEO of Crema, Enrique Paños.
There's a home in Arissola where a Luma Paharac sits near the other end of the home.
gameDescription: Due to their bigger size and stronger physique, Paharac doesn’t actually need camouflage, but they still love to flaunt their turquoise facial feathers with great pride.

name: Granpah
trivia: Granpah's name is derived from Gran Pájaro (Spanish for Grand Bird). It also sounds like Grandpa, a nickname for Grandfather.
Granpah was first seen on a Kickstarter update for types and was later revealed on Twitter.
Prior to the official reveal, clues were given about Granpah's name in the official Temtem Discord. The user who guessed the name correctly was AfroSera#2380.
gameDescription: The authoritative stare of a Granpah portrays the long time and many battles that it takes to achieve this evolutionary stage. They have earned their respect among younger Wind Temtem.

name: Ampling
trivia: Ampling is derived of Ampere and fawnling.
Ampling was originally unnamed #32 on a list of scrapped Temtem that was to be voted to bring back on Kickstarter Update #2.

Ampling was the winner of the Chose a Temtem backer mini-game. Its name was proposed by a community member ( ItsTomas ) in the Official Discord, and later chosen as the winner during the Choose a Temtem names poll in the 6th update of Temtem's Kickstarter.

name: Amphatyr
trivia: Amphatyr is derived from Ampere and Satyr (a woodland deity from Greek mythology).

The name of Amphatyr was proposed by a community member ( ItsTomas ) of the official Discord, and later chosen as the winner during the Choose a Temtem names poll in the 6th update of Temtem's Kickstarter.

name: Bunbun
trivia: Bunbun's name is derived from bùn (Vietnamese for mud) and bunny.
gameDescription: These adorable creatures are probably a remnant from the times Tucma and Kisiwa were a single island. While their strong Earth DNA is clearly of Kisiwan origin, the crystalline contents in their paws betray a definite Tucmani influence. They are social and easy to tame.

name: Mudrid
trivia: Mudrid's name is derived from mud and leoporid (rabbits family scientific name).
gameDescription: Bigger and more resilient than Bunbun, Mudrid are hardy Temtem, used to extreme weather conditions. Their extremely fine sense of hearing makes them very valuable scouting Temtem once tamed... but also harder to catch in the wild.

name: Hidody
trivia: Hidody's name is derived from hide and body.
Hidody was first revealed via Twitter.
gameDescription: This cutie is an adept climber, thanks to the little suckers located in each of its eight stubby legs. For the same reason, Omninesian children quickly learn to hide their cookies instead of putting them on the higher shelf...

name: Taifu
trivia: Taifu's name is derived from tofu (a soft Asian food).
Taifu was first revealed via Twitter.

Ukama Lover an NPC in the residential area of Mokupuni want to trade his Taifu for an Ukama.
The Taifu traded has the same Gender, Level, SVs and remaining Fertility.
The Taifu traded has the same Gender, Level, SVs and remaining Fertility.
gameDescription: Brought up on a steady diet of stolen cookies, Hidody evolves into the more agile Taifu. They are naughty but cute creatures, naturally given to light-hearted mischief... but very serious opponents in battle.

name: Fomu
trivia: Fomu's name is derived from foam.

Due to its first appearance as a cropped picture in the competitive set-up screen (top left, under the player avatar), users in the official Discord attempted to draw out the rest of the creature. Among the drawings, a bird with human-like legs became popular, and thus the name "Legbird" was coined.
gameDescription: These Temtem are known for their capacity to generate vapor, like charming little steam engines. Since that means losing a lot of moisture, this species prefers to remain in the water and use steam jets for propulsion rather than its short legs.

name: Wiplump
trivia: Wiplump's name is derived from wing and plump.
gameDescription: Wiplump takes Fomu's clever use of water vapor one step further - flying on steam wings, this species boasts increased range and speed, paired with a stronger attack thanks to its sturdier horn.

name: Skail
trivia: Skail's name is derived from Skaven and tail.
Skail was first revealed via Twitter.
gameDescription: This species of Temtem is notoriously bad-tempered, and tamers need all their skills to handle them. Once tamed, these muscular creatures can deliver powerful tail blows in battle.

name: Skunch
trivia: Skunch's name is derived from squirrel and punch.
Skunch was first revealed via Twitch in iPokeNinja's Stream on 08/08/2018.
gameDescription: Unlike their lesser brethren, Skunch are capable of bipedalism and can even stand on their muscular tails. This evolution allows them to pummel enemies with their massive fists... but it's done nothing to ameliorate their aggressive mood.

name: Goty
trivia:
Goty's name is derived from a Goat diminutive.
It may also be a pun on the abbreviation for Game of the Year. This is alluded to in its Tempedia entry, which states it's "Voted Best Temtem every year".
It may also be a pun on the abbreviation for Game of the Year. This is alluded to in its Tempedia entry, which states it's "Voted Best Temtem every year".
gameDescription: Voted Best Temtem every year by Neutral enthusiasts, Goty is as effective as it is cute. This little crowd-pleaser is particularly popular among casual Kisiwan tamers.

name: Mouflank
trivia: Mouflank's name is derived from Mouflon and Ankole-Watusi (cattle breed).
gameDescription: With their imposing horns, grazing Mouflank herds used to be serious natural hazards of the Kisiwan plains. The tribes soon learned how to tame them to avoid dangerous stampedes.

name: Rhoulder
trivia: Rhoulder's name is derived from Rhino and Boulder.
Though it lives in an Africa-inspired region, it more closely resembles the Indian Rhinoceros due to the leathery armor it has.
Rhoulder has both the lowest Special Attack stat and the lowest base stat total of any fully evolved Temtem currently available.
gameDescription: Once king of the Kisiwan savannah, this species boasts incredibly hard lamellar plates. Before the time of Chacha Turay, they were used in tribal warfare as armored cavalry.

name: Houchic
trivia: Houchic's name is derived from Houdini and psychic.
The player remarks that Houchic "looks like their old art teacher".
Houchic's appearance strongly resembles that of salamander larvae, making it one of the several known Temtem with this basis.
Houchic and Ganki are tied for the lowest base HP of all Temtem at 38.
gameDescription: Clever but somehow naive, the gentle Houchic are ideal as the first Mental Temtem for novice trainers. They are emphatic and intuitive, capable of understanding the subtleties of mentalism.

name: Tental
trivia: Tental's name is derived from tentacle and mental.
gameDescription: Houchic eventually evolves into the more mature Tental - shrewder creatures, whose writhing tentacles serve as apt metaphors for their ever-twisting, sibylline minds.

name: Nagaise
trivia: Nagaise's name is derived from Naga and Wise.
gameDescription: Cipanki legends are full of sage Nagaise giving cryptic advice to folk heroes - an early example of the traditional association of this species with wisdom, insight, and spirituality.

name: Orphyll
trivia: Orphyll's name is derived from ormr (snake in Old Norse) and chlorophyll.
Orphyll was one of the scrapped Temtem designs that had a chance to be added into the game during the first "Choose a Temtem" mini-game. However, it was not selected in the end.

Orphyll's design had a second chance to be added into the game during the third "Choose a Temtem" mini-game, and ended up winning.
Orphyll's name was submitted by Eggs#8022 during the #035/#036 naming contest, and won with 262 votes.
Orphyll's name was submitted by Eggs#8022 during the #035/#036 naming contest, and won with 262 votes.
gameDescription: Probably a mutation from an ancient serpentine strand of Nature Temtem, Orphyll show remarkable adaptation to noxious conditions. They feature prominently in the art of ancient proto-Arburian cultures, who feared and revered them.

name: Nidrasil
trivia: Nidrasil's name is derived from Níðhöggr (or Nidhogg, a Nordic mythological serpent that means "He who strikes with malice" in old Norse) and Yggdrasil (Nordic tree of life that connects the Nine Worlds together).

Nidrasil's design was revealed during the naming contest for #035 and #036. 
Nidrasil's name was submitted by Eggs#8022 during the #035/#036 contest, and won with 262 votes.
Nidrasil's name was submitted by Eggs#8022 during the #035/#036 contest, and won with 262 votes.
gameDescription: Long considered to be a legend, this species was scientifically verified just decades ago. Temtemologists are still debating how the nervous system of Nidrasil copes with three separate encephalic centers.

name: Banapi
trivia: Banapi's name is derived from  banteng (bull in Indonesian) and api (fire in Indonesian).
Banapi's name was determined through a community naming contest. The winner and creator of the name Banapi was smvid4#0118, from the official Temtem Discord.
gameDescription: Capricious and stubborn, these Temtem roam the side of the Anak volcano, grazing on burning coals instead of grass. Notably difficult to tame, they set the right expectations for prospective Fire Temtem tamers...

name: Capyre
trivia: Capyre's name is derived from capra (genus for goats) and pyre.
Capyre's name was determined through a community naming contest. The winners and creators of the name Capyre were Eggs#8022 and Soma Ghost#4762, from the official Temtem Discord.
gameDescription: These temperamental creatures often appear in Myrislan folklore as tricksters, their unreliable nature embedded deeply in the culture. Highly territorial, they breed in Anak and make sure any visitors know just how unwelcome they are.

name: Lapinite
trivia:
Lapinite's name is derived form lapin (French for Bunny) and ite (suffix for minerals). It is also potentially a pun on Laponite - a kind of synthetic clay.
Lapinite's name was submitted by Matthew#7366 for the #39 naming contest, and won with 198 votes.
Lapinite's name was submitted by Matthew#7366 for the #39 naming contest, and won with 198 votes.
Lapinite's design was revealed during the naming contest for #039.
gameDescription: Extremely common in Tucma, these little creatures are often the first Temtem of every young Quetzaleño. They are cheerful and resistant playmates for toddlers, and it is common practise to lightly file off the edges of their crystals to ensure safety.

name: Azuroc
trivia: Azuroc's name is derived from azure and rock.
gameDescription: This Temtem is a common sight in the Mines of Quetzal, where miners appreciate their skill when dislodging big chunks of ore and gemstones. Its correct and expert handling is a professional requisite for most of them.

name: Zenoreth
trivia:
Zenoreth's name is derived from zenith and ore.
Zenoreth's name was submitted by Eskwyre#9808 during the #39 naming contest, and won with 198 votes.
Zenoreth's name was submitted by Eskwyre#9808 during the #39 naming contest, and won with 198 votes.
Zenoreth's design was revealed during the naming contest for #039.
gameDescription: Any given night at the Jaguar Lounge, drunken miners whisper tall tales about great crystalline behemoths lurking in the darkest abyss under the city. This Temtem is probably the base of all those urban legends... probably.

name: Bigu
trivia: Bigu's name is derived from Bígaro (winkle in Spanish).
Bigu plays a role in the Temtem Connoisseur side-quest.
gameDescription: If there's an easily underestimated Temtem, that's Bigu. Comically ill-tempered, many tamers have found to their cost that these gastropods compensate their slow pace with outstanding tenacity in battle.

name: Babawa
trivia: Babawa's name is derived from baba (slime in Spanish) and agua (water in Spanish).
Babawa currently has the highest base Stamina of all Temtem at 92.
gameDescription: These Temtem are flamboyant creatures with a funky sense of humor and boundless love for pranks and practical jokes. Many a naughty kid has donned a Babawa costume to cause havoc in the Quetzal Carnival.

name: Kaku
trivia: Kaku's name is derived from kakusareta (protected in Japanese).
Kaku was first revealed to the public on Kickstarter update #13.
Kaku has an emote on the official Temtem Discord.
gameDescription: Less known than its evolution, Kaku are delightful creatures, cute beyond description. They tend to keep their petals wrapped around the body for protection, although no sane person would ever want to hurt a Kaku.

name: Saku
trivia: Saku's name is derived from saku (bloom in Japanese, 咲く).
Saku was first revealed via Twitter.
Saku has an emote on the official Temtem Discord.

The Temtem Discord community created "cults" worshipping Saku and Pigepic. The official Twitter account for Temtem later created a tweet pitting the “Sakult” and “Team Porket” against each other. The Sakult is currently the winner.
gameDescription: Some say the first airship designs were inspired by this Temtem's ability to inflate air pockets within its body, allowing it to float and drift with the prevailing winds.

name: Valash
trivia: Valash's name is derived from "vanadinite" and "slash".
A level 35 Valash is gifted to the player as a part of the main story questline Shipwrecked in Tucma!
gameDescription: A fascinating offshoot, Valash is a rare case of bipedal hybrid, documented only recently. The care with which it keeps its forearm crystals sharpened betrays some sort of primitive sentience.

name: Barnshe
trivia: Barnshe's name is derived from barn owl and banshee.
Barnshe was first revealed via Twitter.
Barnshe plays a role in the The Denizan Icarus side-quest.
The first Luma Barnshe was caught by Laknightress (IGN) during Alpha 1, with a 5% encounter rate and 1/4000 Luma chance.
gameDescription: Traditionally associated with the University of Arbury as its heraldic Temtem, this species has a deep, piercing stare. Although winged, it prefers to keep to the ground and use its mind as a weapon - a symbolism the academics are very fond of.

name: Gyalis
trivia: Gyalis's name is derived from gyalisméno (polished in Greek) and mantis.
Gyalis is tied with Ukama and Oceara for the highest base Speed of all Temtem at 100.
gameDescription: Gyalis have appeared in many horror movies. Sadly, this has resulted in a bad reputation as a "scary evil monster", not helped by its menacing appearance - but in the hands of a kind tamer, Gyalis can be every bit as tender and loving as the plushest of Pigepics.

name: Occlura
trivia: Occlura's name is derived from occultatum (hidden in Latin) and lura (mouth in Latin).
gameDescription: Despite its creepy appearance, Occlura are mineral-eaters that never pose any danger to humans. Their tame nature and their appetite for raw rock make them valuable assets for mining purposes, as the Tucmani know very well.

name: Myx
trivia: Myx's name is derived from Mystic and Nyx (the female personification of the night, daughter of Chaos).
gameDescription: The oldest written records in Tucma indicate religious awe of Myx, considered to be embodiments of the "dark spirits". Some were considered to be celestial emissaries of Highabove, some evil messengers of Downbelow... but all were feared. With good reason.

name: Raiber
trivia: Raiber's name is derived from raion (lion in Japanese) and ember.
Raiber was first revealed as a mention on a Twitter post about Raican.
gameDescription: Raiber is often given to novice tamers in Omninesian Dojos because it is relatively mild-mannered for a Fire Temtem. Easier to handle than the mightier varieties, it is nevertheless a loyal companion and decent fighter.

name: Raize
trivia: Raize's name is derived from raion (lion in Japanese) and blaze.
Raize was first revealed through concept art via Twitter.
Animations for idle, physical attack, special attack, and one other were shown off on Twitter.
gameDescription: Fierce and indomitable as the fire, Raize are difficult to tame but extremely valuable as fighting Temtem. Each has a characteristic birthmark on the snout, as unique as the movements of a single flame.

name: Raican
trivia: Raican's name is derived from raion (lion in Japanese) and volcan.
Raican was first revealed via Twitter.
Raican was the first Temtem to be revealed on social media that was directly stated to be a third stage evolution.
gameDescription: As the Tucmani legend goes, at the beginning of time, Tucma and Kisiwa were one single fire plain where huge herds of Raican ran wild and free, flame and Temtem being one until the Archipelago cooled and these noble creatures emigrated underground.

name: Pewki
trivia: Pewki's name is derived from pewa (dorsal fin in Hawaiian) and iki (small in Hawaiian)

Pewki has the lowest base stat total of all Temtem at 263 and the lowest base Special Defense of all Temtem at 10.
In addition, it is tied with Goolder for having the lowest single base stat of any Temtem.
In addition, it is tied with Goolder for having the lowest single base stat of any Temtem.
gameDescription: Their flat shape allows Pewki to float right under the water surface, while they scout around using their huge, widely spaced eyes. Their iconic tall fins are often the only way to tell them apart from driftwood.

name: Piraniant
trivia: Piraniant's name is derived from piranha and giant.
Piraniant was first revealed via Twitter.
Piraniant has an emote on the official Temtem discord.
gameDescription: A native species of Deniz, this Temtem tends to drift with the Sillaro current, to conserve energy... but once brought into battle, its size makes it a powerful fighter.

name: Osuchi
trivia: Osuchi's name is derived from Osu (Japanese expression for martial arts) and Chi (earth in Japanese).
gameDescription: Shy and unassuming, Osuchi are generally considered benevolent, steadfast friends. Often confused with rock outcroppings by the untrained eye, they are at home in the Jino Gap.

name: Osukan
trivia: Osukan's name is derived from Osu (Japanese expression for martial arts) and Keikan (rooster's crest in Japanese).
gameDescription: Osukan are the perfect embodiment of the endurance and grit of the best Temtem fighters. They are sturdy, obstinate creatures that love nothing better than to show their prowess in a hard, honest battle against a worthy rival.

name: Osukai
trivia: Osukai's name is derived from Osu (Japanese expression for martial arts) and "Tatakai" (battle in Japanese).
The name Osukai was revealed in the official Discord on the 13th of July 2020.
Osukai was first shown on the printed sticker pack in the Kickstarter physical rewards status and progress update.
gameDescription: Massive, four-armed Osukai are as hard as granite. They are credited with much of the boring heavy-lifting during the construction of the tunnels under the Kilima Range.

name: Saipat
trivia: Saipat's name is derived from sai (a prong-shaped melee weapon) and pato ("duck" in Spanish), or platypus (billed mammal).
Saipat first appeared as small pieces of an image that were slowly revealed in the official Temtem Discord, until fans guessed its design while creating fan art.
Purple paint is traditionally made from the discarded shells of growing Saipat. They are carefully collected from where the young adult Saipat discard them, then crushed into a fine powder.
Saipat is likely a parody of the Pokémon Psyduck. (In English, sai and psy are pronounced the same way.)
gameDescription: Nothing says 'amateur' like making fun of Saipat. Sure, they might look comical at first sight, but nobody who has faced a totally focused Saipat, sturdy coral sai in hand, takes them anything but seriously.

name: Pycko
trivia: Pycko's name is derived from Pyre and Gecko.
gameDescription: Bubbly and cheerful, this Temtem is the protagonist of an animation series aimed at warning children of the dangers of fire. It has been a lifelong friend to many first-time tamers.

name: Drakash
trivia: Drakash's name is derived from Draak (dragon in Afrikaans) and Ash.
gameDescription: Selective breeding for bipedalism meant this variety of Temtem is faster and more suited for human tasks than its predecessors. Often given as a New Year's gift between Kisiwans and Tucmani.

name: Crystle
trivia: Crystle's name is derived from crystal and turtle.
gameDescription: Native to Tucma, Crystle are akin to smaragdine turtles, but they are actually closer to minerals than to fauna. Cute but tough, they are an excellent introductory Crystal Temtem for rookie tamers.

name: Sherald
trivia: Sherald's name is derived from shell and emerald.
gameDescription: Sherald are known to evolve from Crystle- in the wild, as a result of exposure to the harsh environmental conditions of Tucma. They extract nutrients from the chemical interactions of metamorphic rocks and volcanic ashes.

name: Tortenite
trivia: Tortenite's name is derived from Tortoise and Torbenite.
As of Alpha 0.6.9, Tortenite awards the most total TVs (5) of any known Temtem. It is tied with Seismunch.
gameDescription: Tortenite are lumbering creatures, often employed by Tucmani miners as work companions. In the wild, they are often spotted herding Sherald as pack leaders.

name: Hocus
trivia: Hocus' name is derived from "Hocus Pocus" (a common phrase attributed to magicians and witches).
Hocus is Lady Lottie's signature Temtem.
gameDescription: Arcane and blue-blooded, Hocus have been selectively bred for generations and kept as dynastic heirlooms of the House of Braeside. They are fine weapons, trained to be battle Temtem for the ancient aristocracy, a rare sight nowadays.

name: Pocus
trivia: Pocus' name is derived from Hocus Pocus (a common phrase attributed to magicians and witches).
gameDescription: Pocus was considered blue-blooded among the blue bloods, and was traditionally given only to the male heirs of the House of Braeside. When the lineage fell, they mostly went extinct... until recently.

name: Sparzy
trivia: Sparzy's name is derived from spark and  crazy.
Sparzy was first revealed unnamed via Twitter.
Sparzy’s name came from Yerin's suggestion on Twitter.
Sparzy has an emote on the official Temtem discord.
What might be an earlier evolution-stage of Sparzy can be seen in the official Anime-styled trailer of Temtem. It has a very strong resemblance to Sparzy in both color scheme and shape.
gameDescription: Also known familiarly as "Sparky", this Temtem is a common sight in Cipanku. Children are warned to keep away from them - although normally good-natured and cheerful, they can involuntarily discharge considerable electric shocks.

name: Mushi
trivia: Mushi's name is derived from a mushroom diminutive.
gameDescription: Closely related to the non-sentient fungi of the Corrupted Badlands, Mushi are shy but territorial. Always mineral-hungry, wise tamers keep them well away from Crystal Temtem.

name: Mushook
trivia: Mushook's name is derived from mushroom and hook.
gameDescription: Mushook are a hybrid variety, developed at the Quetzal Dojo by expert breeders. Strong and single-minded, some of the bigger specimens are occasionally employed by the Guards as static sentries at strategic points.

name: Magmis
trivia: Magmis' name is derived from malleus (hammer in Latin) and ignis (fire in Latin).
Magmis was first revealed via Twitter.
Magmis was the first Temtem with a confirmed evolution.
gameDescription: Magmis' original habitat was in the lava rivers under the Anak caldera, but now they can be found all around the Archipelago, as foundry operators in Quetzal, heating systems in Arbury... And, of course, in Temtem battles.

name: Mastione
trivia: Mastione's name is derived from malleus (hammer in Latin) and combustione (combustion in Latin).
Mastione was first revealed via Twitter.
Mastione was the first Temtem with a confirmed pre-evolution.
gameDescription: Mastione are fire-loving Temtem, at home in the fiercest of blazes. They can be found grazing in woods devoured by wildfire. The tamed varieties learn to rein in their destructive tendencies - but even then, trainers should exercise care.

name: Umishi
trivia:
Umishi's name is derived from umi (sea in Japanese) and tenshi (angel in Japanese).
The name Umishi was suggested by Ava Duhrkopp#4286 of the Temtem Discord in the Temtem naming suggestion poll from September 24 2018.
The name Umishi was suggested by Ava Duhrkopp#4286 of the Temtem Discord in the Temtem naming suggestion poll from September 24 2018.
The overall design seems to be based off salamander larvae. This would make it one of the several known temtems to be based off salamanders.
Umishi was first seen in iNinjaHero's Twitch stream on 08/08/2018.
gameDescription: The Umishi feature in many Denizan tales, usually saving drowning sailors and helping them get to shore. These so-called "sea-angels" are dependable friends, and the Riverine Fellowship recommends every member keep at least one in their squad.

name: Ukama
trivia:
Ukama's name is derived from umi (sea in Japanese) and kama (sickle in Japanese).
The name Ukama was suggested by YamaXenuz#8049 of the Temtem Discord in the Temtem naming suggestion poll from September 24 2018
The name Ukama was suggested by YamaXenuz#8049 of the Temtem Discord in the Temtem naming suggestion poll from September 24 2018
Ukama is tied with Oceara and Gyalis for the highest base Speed stat of all Temtem at 100.
During alpha testing, Ukama was known for a bug in the first phase that hard-locked tamers in battle sequences with it. This bug was fixed after a bit of difficulty.

Ukama Lover an NPC in the residential area of Mokupuni want to trade his Taifu for an Ukama.
The Taifu traded has the same Gender, Level, SVs and remaining Fertility.
The Taifu traded has the same Gender, Level, SVs and remaining Fertility.
gameDescription: Ukama, also known in Turquesa as "sea-sickles", are one of the fastest waterborne Temtem. They can easily outrun the sleekest sailboat, even swimming against the Sillaro current, so tamers have to use charm and guile to approach them.

name: Raignet
trivia: Raignet's name is derived from Ray and Magnet.
Raignet was first revealed via Twitter.
gameDescription: When suddenly all the cutlery in your kitchen flies out of the window, you know this Temtem is nearby. In fact, it uses its magnetic power to move its own heavy, metallic body. The Cipanki always keep them away from their fridges.

name: Smazee
trivia: Smazee's name is derived from smack and chimpanzee.
gameDescription: These little darlings have been bred for generations as playmates and babysitters for children - although capable fighters, Smazee are naturally cheerful and love playing and monkeying around.

name: Baboong
trivia: Baboong's name is derived from baboon and young.
gameDescription: Baboong are evolved, street-fighting Temtem, very popular in Lochburg, where they are often employed by pub bouncers. Although naturally good-tempered, they are as fierce as their hot-headed tamers.

name: Seismunch
trivia: Seismunch's name is derived from Seismic and Punch.
Seismunch could be loosely based on Sun Wukong the monkey king born of stone from the book the journey to the west.
As of Alpha 0.6.9, Seismunch awards the most total TVs (5) of any known Temtem. It is tied with Tortenite.
gameDescription: Seismunch are great apes, genetically close to humans and much more sophisticated than their lesser brethren. Highly imitative of human behavior, some are said to be nearing proto-human cognition.

name: Zizare
trivia: Zizare's name is derived from Zizare (worm in Basque).
Zizare was first seen through the Kickstarter Video then fully revealed on Twitter.
gameDescription: One of the most remarkable inhabitants of the Kisiwan savanna, the powerful Zizare are the biggest creeping Temtem. Proud and territorial, they make for staunch friends.

name: Momo
trivia: Momo is a Breeder Tier Temtem by Kyle, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. He came up with the idea of a Siberian Husky-like Temtem and gave Crema complete freedom for the name and Luma coloration.
Momo is named after Guillermo “YaW” Andrades’ Shiba Inu dog. Its Luma color scheme is also based on YaW's dog.
Momo's cry resembles the "woof" barking sound of a dog.
This is the only known Temtem with heterochromia (having different iris colors).
gameDescription: While some Temtemologist point to the primeval forests of Arbury and Cipanku as possible origin of this species, there is plenty of archaeological proof of their early domestication around Lake Moyo.

name: Kuri
trivia: Kuri's name is derived from a Kura diminutive (hyena in Hausa).
gameDescription: Another great example of adaptation to the environment, these little Temtem select and carve rocks to use as protection for their heads and snouts.

name: Kauren
trivia: Kauren's name is derived from Kura (hyena in Hausa) and Hauren giwa (ivory in Hausa).
gameDescription: Not to be confused with their previous evolution stage, Kauren develops stone-hard horns and skull extensions - used for digging out roots, defense and status-signalling within the herd.

name: Spriole
trivia: Spriole's name is derived from sprout and petiole.
gameDescription: These little sprouts are a common sight along the Omninesian canopy, and the locals are always gentle with them. These little pups are playful and juvenile.

name: Deendre
trivia: Deendre's name is derived from deer and cendre (ash tree in French).
gameDescription: The young adult version of Spriole, Deendre are fascinating plant-animal hybrids that use their encephalic leaves to produce healing and nourishing components via photosynthesis.

name: Cerneaf
trivia: Cerneaf's name is derived from Cernunnos (Celtic deer God) and leaf.
Cerneaf was first revealed via Twitter.
gameDescription: Few Temtem are closer to flora than this species, a fascinating plant-animal hybrid that uses its encephalic leaves to produce healing and nourishing components via photosynthesis.

name: Toxolotl
trivia: Toxolotl's name is derived from toxic and axolotl.
gameDescription: Perhaps no other Temtem is as representative of Tucma as the colorful Toxolotl. Each strand in its mane is supposed to signify one of the original Tucmani tribes that first excavated and settled Quetzal after the Anak cataclysm.

name: Noxolotl
trivia: Noxolotl's name comes from the combination of the words noxious and axolotl.
Despite it’s highest stat being special attack, it was unable to learn any special attacks until the update following it's release.
gameDescription: Noxolotl are noble, dignified creatures. They are taken to exemplify the resilience and spirit of the Tucmani people, as "a beauty born of the foulest depths of Xolot, a light in the abyss", in the words of the poetess Itzia.

name: Blooze
trivia: Blooze's name is derived fromblob and ooze.
gameDescription: Blooze represent the opposite evolutionary path as compared to Toxolotl - blobby and bipedal, they are probably the oldest lifeform of Xolot, an atavic variety still largely unexplained by science.

name: Goolder
trivia: Goolder's name is derived from goo and elder.

Goolder has the highest HP stat of all Temtem at 125.
Due to this, Goolder has the highest single base stat of any Temtem
Due to this, Goolder has the highest single base stat of any Temtem

Goolder has the lowest Speed stat of all Temtem at 10.
Its tied with Pewki for having the lowest single base stat of any Temtem.
Its tied with Pewki for having the lowest single base stat of any Temtem.
As of Alpha 0.6.9, Goolder is the heaviest known Temtem, over 3 times heavier than the second heaviest known (Tortenite)
gameDescription: Not many agree to classify Goolder as an "evolution", for many of its traits seem to be vestigial features of a more complex organism, devolved to a more primitive or atrophied state. Its lack of legs is usually cited as an example... but its haphazard appearance conceals great strength.

name: Zephyruff
trivia: Zephyruff is a Breeder Tier Temtem by Soma Ghost, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. The design process for Zephyruff and Volarend was originally shown on the "Presenting our first Breeder Temtem" Kickstarter update.
Zephyruff was nicknamed by Manly Fairy in a community poll for the name. Despite Entu and Siotu being the leading names, Soma Ghost decided on Zephyruff and Volarend before the polling finished.

Zephyruff's name is derived from Zephyr (a gentle breeze or wind along with deriving from Zephyros, the Greek God of the West Wind) and Ruff (a piece of clothing that was popular during the sixteenth and seventeenth century with more modern uses being by Bishops).
gameDescription: Awkward fliers at best, Zephyruff rely on their speed and sharp claws to defend themselves. The sturdy, cloud-like tissue around the neck serves a double purpose, offering protection for the mother Temtem as well as a roosting point for Zephyruff chicks.

name: Volarend
trivia: Volarend is a Breeder Tier Temtem by Soma Ghost, who pledged $6000 to the Kickstarter. The design process for Zephyruff and Volarend was originally shown on the "Presenting our first Breeder Temtem" Kickstarter update.
Volarend was nicknamed by Manly Fairy in a community poll for the name. Despite Entu and Siotu being the leading names, Soma Ghost decided on Zephyruff and Volarend before the polling finished.
Volarend's name is derived from Volare (fly or to fly in Latin and Italian) and Rend.
Volarend was originally referred to by the community as "Zabirdo", a variation on "the bird".
gameDescription: Volarend are impressive avians of great wingspan, strong enough to carry humans in flight. However, they are temperamental and picky mounts, and tamers are well-advised to treat them kindly, lest they are given a one-way ticket to the Downbelow...

name: Grumvel
trivia: Grumvel's name is derived from Grumpy and Gravel.
gameDescription: "Sulky as a Grumvel" is a common Uhurian idiom, usually addressed at comically malcontent little kids.

name: Grumper
trivia: Grumper's name is derived from Grumpy and Thunder.
gameDescription: Often the butt of Dojo jokes, Grumper are an evolutive mystery. While some Temtemologists claim they are just Grumvel with overdeveloped horns, some others claim it's a completely different genus.

name: Ganki
trivia: Ganki's name is derived from ga (moth in Japanese) and denki (electric current in Japanese).
Ganki was first revealed via Twitter.
Ganki has an emote on the official Temtem discord.
Ganki is tied with Houchic for the lowest base HP of all Temtem at 38.
gameDescription: Many Cipanki legends mention the kind but powerful Ganki as mountain spirits, mythologically related to lightning and whirlwinds. Although they are no longer revered as kami, the Cipanki still appreciate and breed them.

name: Gazuma
trivia: Gazuma's name is derived from Ga (moth in Japanese) and Inazuma (lightning strike in Japanese).
gameDescription: Even in the wild, younger Ganki seem to instinctively respect them as their elders. In the hills of Iwaba, one can often spot Gazuma leading small flocks of Ganki, a clear indication of their status among Electric Temtem.

name: Oceara
trivia: Oceara's name is derived from ocean and Mearas Mearas (a breed of wild horses from The Lord of the Rings).
Oceara has the highest base stat total of all Water type Temtem at 486.
Oceara is tied with Gyalis and Ukama for the highest base Speed of all Temtem at 100.
Oceara appeared for the first time in the Mounts Kickstarter update, though little was known about it. Its official name and description were revealed on the official Temtem Twitter on 19/11/2018.
Oceara seems to be based off the Qilin/Kirin, antelopine divine creatures in Chinese and Japanese mythology respectively.
gameDescription: Very rarely seen in Deniz, Oceara are believed to be the basis for the legendary "serbatiyo" of the Sea-Queen legend. Their possession is a mark of distinction and prestige among Water Temtem experts.

name: Yowlar
trivia: Yowlar's name is derived from Yowie (Australian folklore creature similar to the Yeti) and Polar.
Yowlar has the highest base stat total of any currently available Temtem.
gameDescription: Considered vanishingly rare until Linnaea's work, this lonesome Temtem inhabits the most inaccessible Kilima peaks, where they keep large, fiercely defended hunting ranges.

name: Droply
trivia: Droply's name is derived from Droplet and Baby.
gameDescription: Although not particularly popular among tamers, Droply is used by many scholars as a prime example of an early Archipelagian amphibian, a crucial link in the evolution of earthborne Temtem.

name: Garyo
trivia: Garyo's name is derived from Gregarious and Lake Moyo.
gameDescription: Semiaquatic and very gregarious, they are often found along the shores of Lake Moyo, where local farmers train them to harvest seaweed and warn away any boats with their sonorous hisses.

name: Shuine
trivia: Shuine's name is derived from shui (water in Chinese) and pristine.
Shuine is based on the feathered deities of Mesoamerican religions, with western dragon ears.
gameDescription: Colorful Shuine are a sight to behold, their bright scales reflecting Pansunlight as they frolic in the Kakama Cenote. They feed off the acidic components of Xolotic water, acting as natural filters and keeping cenote waters clean and fit for human consumption almost as effectively as the layers of volcanic rock.

name: Nessla
trivia: Nessla's name is derived from Nessy (likely a reference to the Loch Ness Monster whom is affectionately known as "Nessie") and Tesla (Nikola Tesla was a famous scientist who developed the alternating current (AC) electricity supply system).
Nessla was originally unnamed #33 on a list of scrapped Temtem that was to be voted to bring back on Kickstarter Update #2.

Nessla was one of the two winners of the Choose a Temtem backer mini-game during the Kickstarter. Its name was proposed by a community member (JMick) in Official Discord, and later chosen as the winner during the Choose a Temtem names poll in the 6th update of Temtem's Kickstarter.
A Nessla is given to the player as a part of the main story quest Shipwrecked in Tucma!
gameDescription: Water and electricity are always a dangerous mix - and it's never as true as in the case of Nessla. These undulating, majestic creatures are at home in open waters, where their powerful electric discharges are most effective.

name: Valiar
trivia: Valiar's name is derived from Vacio (empty in Spanish) and Ampliar (extend in Spanish referencing them using their ear holes to amplify their mental powers).
Valiar was first revealed through its early concept art via Twitter.

Valiar looks very different in its concept art compared to its final design. The main colouration is a dark and light purple, and Valiar is generally depicted with a stripe pattern instead of a spot pattern. In addition, some key details like the thick neck tuft are not present. The eyes have a completely different shape and color compared to the final version.
gameDescription: Although nobody has managed to decipher their language, the Valiar are assumed to be extremely intelligent. The Arburian dons are still trying to come up with a scientific explanation for the way Valiar use their expanding ears to boost their minds.

name: Kalazu
trivia: Kalazu's name is derived from Calamari and Azure.
Kalazu was revealed to the public on Kickstarter update #13.
Kalazu's name was suggested by the discord user Yobri#7969 in the naming suggestion poll from August 14.
gameDescription: Kalazu show remarkable fine motor skills with each of their tentacles. "Send Kalazu!" is a common expression of woe in Deniz. When you face a hard task, you might need a hand - when you need eight hands... well, you're in trouble.

name: Kalabyss
trivia: Kalabyss' name is derived from Calamari and Abyss.
Kalabyss was revealed to the public on the official discord and the Kickstarter update #30.

Kalabyss' name (originally Calabyss) was suggested by the discord user lepastro#3547 in the naming suggestion poll from August 14 and was later modified to Kalabyss to better match its pre-evolutions name.
gameDescription: How did Sillarian octopoda come in contact with mutagenic material is a matter of debate, but Kalabyss stand as an example of extreme adaption to the harshest environments - they have been known to survive a swim in Xolot Reservoir.

name: Adoroboros
trivia: Adoroboros' name derived from adorable and ouroboros (a famous Egyptian symbol depicting a serpent or dragon eating its tail and is notable in its use in alchemy.)
Adoroboros has the highest base Special Defense of any temtem.

Adoroboros was originally shown on the Choose-a-Temtem V3 poll, currently unnamed. It got second place with 554 votes, just 25 votes behind the winner.
Adoroboros was first nicknamed Adoroboros by Temtem Discord community member Husky. The nickname was later put into an official poll for naming the Temtem by the Discord member TMTrainer. It won the poll with 157 votes, becoming the official name of #129.

Adoroboros was first nicknamed Adoroboros by Temtem Discord community member Husky. The nickname was later put into an official poll for naming the Temtem by the Discord member TMTrainer. It won the poll with 157 votes, becoming the official name of #129.
gameDescription: Few Temtem are as deceptive as Adoroboros - an unusual mix of cute and deadly, combining the most sophisticated Mental tricks with the basest Toxic traits. They are a fine example of the incredible natural diversity of the Archipelago.

name: Tuwai
trivia: Tuwai's name is derived from tukana (toucan in Hawaiian) and wai (juice in Hawaiian).
gameDescription: Professor Konstantinos described Tuwai as “taxonomically Wind, but also the only Denizan Temtem with meta-mimetic properties.” He theorized about the possibility of Tuwai changing dramatically “if the relevant Place of Power” could be found.

name: Tukai
trivia: Tukai's name is derived from Tukana (tucan in Hawaiian) and Kai (sea in Hawaiian).
gameDescription: It is unclear whether Professor Konstantinos ever discovered this evolution, with its flaming aquamarine wings - a true feat of meta-mimetic evolution, unseen elsewhere in the whole Archipelago.

name: Tuvine
trivia: Tuvine's name derives from Tukana (toucan in Hawaian) and Olivine.
Tuvine has the highest base Defense of all Temtem at 111.
gameDescription: Just how a Crystal Temtem manages to fly effectively is still a mystery to most Temtemologists. Some theorize its flight is aided by magnetic repulsion generated by mineral organs... but most tamers just enjoy their emerald majesty without asking too many questions.

name: Turoc
trivia: Turoc's name is derived from Tukana (Tucan in Hawaiian) and Rock.
It might also be a pun on the Turok video game series.
gameDescription: Turoc is, in the words of Linnaea, "a meeting of opposites - a flying rock, stone on wings - an impossibility, and yet, a reality (...) further proof of the marvelous diversity of Temtem lifeforms."

name: Kinu
trivia: Kinu's name is derived from Kinushi (forest spirits in Japanese culture).
Kinu is shown on the thumbnail of the Kickstarter trailer.
It is also on the Kickstarter exclusive painted statue alongside a Temtem Tamer.
gameDescription: The elusive Kinu are some of the rarest Nature Temtem in the Myrisles - to the point that some tamers think they're a mere legend. When they do show up, Omninesians treat them with the respect reserved for the guardian spirits of the Banyan.

name: Vulvir
trivia: Vulvir's name is derived from Vulcan (Roman God of fire) and hervir (boil in Spanish).
gameDescription: Some academics speculate that this is the last remnant of a long-lost "Draconic" variety of Temtem. In practice terms, most tamers classify them as Fire-Earth, which is an accurate designator for these mighty but shy creatures.

name: Vulor
trivia: Needed for quest If You Build It
Vulor's name is derived from Vulcano (Roman God of fire) and calor (heat in Spanish).
gameDescription: Although they hide their faces in hollow rocks like their lesser brethren, these Temtem have very little to fear from their environment. Tough as stone and destructive as fire, they are a force to be reckoned with.

name: Vulcrane
trivia: Vulcrane's name is derived from Vulcan (Roman God of fire) and Cráneo (cranium in Spanish).
gameDescription: Vulcrane are sometimes described as "Anak on two legs". If a variety of draconic-looking Temtem ever existed, they couldn't have been much fiercer than this advanced, flaming beast.

name: Pigepic
trivia: Pigepic's name is derived from pig and epic.
Pigepic's design is likely based on the English phrase, "when pigs fly", which is used to describe an impossible situation.
Despite being Temtem number #141, Pigepic was the first Temtem to be revealed to the public via Twitter.
Pigepic has two emotes on the official Temtem discord, originally alongside Pewki's single emote.

The Temtem Discord community created "cults" worshiping Saku and Pigepic. The official Twitter account for Temtem later created a tweet pitting the “Sakult” and “Team Porket” against each other. The Sakult is currently the winner.
gameDescription: The absolute favourites of toddlers all around the Archipelago, Pigepic are fluffy, soft and absolutely adorable. Voluminous and cumbersome, they normally float low over the ground, making them ideal playmates for small children.

name: Akranox
trivia: Akranox's name is derived from Akrabuamelu (scorpion deity) and Noxious.
gameDescription: Well-armed with a mighty stinger and protected by rugged rock-like armor, Akranox can afford to have flash colored pincers and a cocky attitude, making them a favorite of Archipelagian teens.

name: Koish
gameDescription: Unique amongst all Temtem, Koish sub-species are known to span all Temtem types. This extreme range of diversity is attributed to early mutations in the Xolotic-Moyoan-Sillarin ocean of prehistoric Paninsula.

name: Vulffy
trivia: Vulffy's name is derived from Vulpes (fox in Latin) and Fluffy.
gameDescription: Extremely perceptive and aware, this species flourishes (in all senses of the word) in the great expanses of wild land - although they are inquisitive by nature, and never shy away from human contact.

name: Anahir
trivia:
Anahir's name is derived from Anak and Terlahir (born in Indonesian), so its name means "Born from Anak".
Its name was for a while rumored to be Rihanna backwards, which was "confirmed" on Twitter while CEO Tateru was in control on April 1st, 2020.
Its name was for a while rumored to be Rihanna backwards, which was "confirmed" on Twitter while CEO Tateru was in control on April 1st, 2020.
The Anahir you obtain during the quest Adventure in the Myrisles will always have 50 SVs in both DEF and SPDEF stats.
Players can decide to not obtain Anahir to save storage, useful for those who value storage for FreeTem. Similarly players can decide to obtain Anahir at a later date.
The Crystal Temtem that was subjected to intense heat to create Anahir is not a reference to any specific Temtem.
gameDescription: This tortured creature is the result of Dr. Hamijo's attempts at creating a new "Diamond" variety. By picking the sturdiest variety of Crystal Temtem and submitting it to the harshest Fire environment of Anak, he has achieved something unique... and uniquely cruel.
